HEADWORD: obligated
<hw>obligated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>under a moral
obligation to someone.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> beholden(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>under a legal obligation to someone.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> indebted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>owing gratitude or recognition to another for help
or favors etc. Opposite of <ant>unobligated</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>supposed(predicate), required </stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> indebted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obligation</ent>⟦br⟧
